    <article class="content-article">
      <p>I've replaced hundreds of LG dryer motors over the past decade, and nine times out of ten, homeowners call us after hearing that grinding noise for weeks thinking it'll just go away. The motor is the heart of your dryer — when it starts failing, that rhythmic humming turns into an expensive problem that won't fix itself.</p>

      <h2>Signs Your LG Dryer Motor Needs Professional Replacement</h2>
      <p>The first thing we check when a customer calls about their dryer not starting is the motor assembly. Most homeowners don't realize that LG dryer motors give you plenty of warning before they completely fail. You'll hear grinding or squealing during the spin cycle, or the drum might turn slowly even though the motor is running. We've seen motors in Pasadena homes struggle for months before homeowners realize it's not just a belt issue. The telltale sign? Your dryer starts fine but stops mid-cycle, then won't restart for 20-30 minutes. That's the thermal overload protection kicking in because your motor is overheating. Don't ignore these symptoms — a failing motor puts stress on other components like the control board and thermal fuse.</p>

      <h3>Common Motor Failure Symptoms in LG Models</h3>
      <p>LG's ThinQ and Signature series have specific motor patterns we've learned to recognize. The DLGX and DLEX models tend to develop bearing wear around the 7-8 year mark, creating that distinctive metallic grinding sound. If your dryer is making noise but still drying clothes, you've got maybe 2-3 weeks before complete failure.</p>

      <h2>Why DIY Motor Replacement Usually Backfires</h2>
      <p>I've seen too many weekend warriors attempt LG motor replacements only to call us Monday morning with a bigger mess. The motor assembly connects to multiple safety systems — thermal fuses, door switches, and moisture sensors. One wrong wire connection and you're looking at a fire hazard or a control board replacement that costs more than the original repair. LG uses specific torque specs for motor mounting bolts, and their wiring harnesses have particular routing requirements. We use OEM parts exclusively because aftermarket motors don't have the same electrical characteristics. The voltage curves are different, which confuses the dryer's computer. Most homeowners also don't realize they need to calibrate the new motor with LG's diagnostic mode after installation.</p>

      <h3>Hidden Costs of DIY Gone Wrong</h3>
      <p>We've rescued dozens of DIY attempts where homeowners damaged the drum housing trying to access the motor. What started as a $200 motor replacement becomes a $400 repair when you factor in the damaged parts. Plus, attempting your own repair voids LG's remaining warranty coverage.</p>

      <h2>Our Professional Motor Replacement Process</h2>
      <p>When we arrive for a motor replacement, the first 15 minutes involve testing everything connected to that motor. We verify the control board is sending proper signals and check all safety switches before touching a single bolt. Our techs disconnect power at the breaker — never just unplug the unit — because LG dryers store electrical charge in their capacitors. The motor assembly removal requires specific positioning of the drum and careful disconnection of the moisture sensor wires. We photograph every connection before disconnecting anything. Installation of the new OEM motor involves precise belt tensioning and verification that the drum spins freely without binding. The final step is running LG's built-in diagnostic cycle to ensure all systems communicate properly with the new motor.</p>

      <h3>Testing and Calibration After Installation</h3>
      <p>Every LG dryer has a hidden diagnostic mode that checks motor performance under various load conditions. We run three complete test cycles to verify proper operation before considering the job finished. This catches issues that might not show up during normal use.</p>

      <h2>Motor Availability and Timing in LA Area</h2>
      <p>We stock the most common LG motor assemblies on our trucks, which covers about 70% of the models we see in LA and Orange County. For specialty models like the Signature series or older DLGX units, we can usually source OEM parts same-day from our supplier network. The actual replacement takes 45-60 minutes once we have the right motor. We've found that LG motors manufactured after 2018 have better longevity than earlier versions, so if your dryer is from that era, the replacement motor should give you 8-10 years of reliable service. Most customers are surprised how quiet their dryer runs after motor replacement — they'd gotten used to the noise gradually increasing over months.</p>

      <h3>OEM vs Aftermarket Motor Quality</h3>
      <p>We've tested aftermarket motors and consistently see premature failures within 18 months. LG's OEM motors use better bearing materials and have tighter manufacturing tolerances. The $30 savings isn't worth the hassle of another service call next year.</p>

      <h2>When Motor Replacement Makes Financial Sense</h2>
      <p>The honest truth? If your LG dryer is over 12 years old and the motor dies, we usually recommend replacement rather than repair. But for units 5-10 years old, motor replacement is almost always the smart financial choice. A new motor assembly runs $180-220 depending on your model, plus labor. Compare that to $800-1200 for a comparable new LG dryer. We've replaced motors in units that ran perfectly for another 5+ years afterward. The key is making sure no other major components are failing simultaneously. That's why our diagnostic process checks the control board, heating element, and moisture sensors before we recommend motor replacement.</p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I know if my LG dryer motor needs replacement?</h3>
      <p>Listen for grinding, squealing, or unusual humming sounds during operation. If your dryer starts but stops mid-cycle, then won't restart for 20-30 minutes, that's the motor overheating and triggering thermal protection. We can run diagnostics to confirm motor failure versus other issues like bad belts or seized drum bearings.</p>

      <h3>How long does LG dryer motor replacement take?</h3>
      <p>About 45-60 minutes for the actual replacement once we have the correct motor assembly. Add another 30 minutes for testing and calibration. If we need to order a specific motor for your model, that's usually same-day delivery in the LA area, so total time from diagnosis to completion is typically 2-3 hours.</p>

      <h3>Can I replace my LG dryer motor myself?</h3>
      <p>I wouldn't recommend it. LG motors connect to multiple safety systems and require specific wiring configurations. One wrong connection creates a fire hazard. Plus, the new motor needs calibration through LG's diagnostic mode. We've seen too many DIY attempts that caused more damage than the original problem.</p>

      <h3>What does LG dryer motor replacement cost?</h3>
      <p>Total cost is usually $280-320 including the OEM motor assembly and labor. We charge $65 for diagnosis, but that's waived if you proceed with the repair. Aftermarket motors are cheaper but fail within 18 months — stick with OEM parts for long-term reliability.</p>

      <h3>Will replacing the motor fix all my dryer problems?</h3>
      <p>Motor replacement fixes motor-related issues like failure to start, stopping mid-cycle, or unusual noises. But if your dryer isn't heating properly or clothes come out damp, those are separate problems. Our diagnostic process identifies all issues before we start any work, so there are no surprises.</p>

      <h2>Schedule Same-Day LG Dryer Repair</h2>
      <p>If your LG dryer motor is showing signs of failure, don't wait for complete breakdown. Call (323) 990-7550 and we'll schedule same-day service Monday through Saturday, 8am to 8pm. Our $65 diagnostic fee gets waived when you proceed with repair, and we stock most LG motor assemblies on our trucks for immediate replacement. You'll get OEM parts, professional installation, and the peace of mind that comes with our 4.9-star rating and BBB A+ certification.</p>
